title: Prep Profile: Travis Clary, Winnebago Lutheran
text:
Prep Profile: Travis Clary, Winnebago Lutheran Sam Oleson , Action Reporter Media 12:33 p.m. CDT October 19, 2015 Winnebago Lutheran's Travis Clary talks about his junior season of boys soccer for the Vikings. Winnebago Lutheran’s Travis Clary is the leading scorer for the Vikings in 2015. (Photo: Sam Oleson/Action Reporter Media) 15 CONNECT 6 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Winnebago Lutheran, Junior, Boys Soccer 
Sports Travis competes in 
Soccer 
Travis’ week 
The Vikings’ leading scorer in 2015, Clary had an assist in Winnebago Lutheran’s 5-0 win over Omro last Monday and followed that up with two goals in a 10-0 victory over Mayville on Tuesday. He then scored twice in the Vikings’ regular-season finale against Central Wisconsin Christian on Thursday, a 7-0 win. On the season, Clary has 22 goals and five assists for a total of 49 points. 
All-time team sports achievement 
Advancing to the Wisconsin State Cup as a member of the Appleton Soccer Club last summer 
No. 1 athletic goal 
Getting recognized as an all-conference player in the Flyway Conference 
Travis’ thoughts 
“I like it when we play as a team. I’m more of a team player, I don’t really believe in the whole one-man team thing. I like playing with other players and getting more goals for the whole team.” 
Coach David Haag’s thoughts 
“Travis is a cliche. He’s a coach’s cliche. He’s our most-skilled player all-around and our hardest working player. He just loves soccer so much. He runs his guts out all the time, he’s very intense. He’s self-motivated. He doesn’t really need a coach. He’s self-coached. He plays a lot in the offseason, he gets guys fired up on the field. He doesn’t need to be encouraged to be intense or to work on things. He’s one of those guys that’s just a dream to coach because he’s highly skilled, he’s your hardest-working guy and he loves the game.” 
Travis’ favorites 
•Pro/college athlete: Professional soccer player Cristiano Ronaldo 
•Pro/college team: University of Wisconsin men’s soccer team 
•Musical artist: Fetty Wap 
•Song of all time: “300 Violin Orchestra” by Jorge Quintero 
•TV show: “Sherlock Holmes”
